SEARCH

Unnamed Package

  • Class
    Description
    ContextFreeGrammar
    Represents a context-free grammar with variables, terminals, rules, and a start symbol.
    Format
    This class defines characters that correspond to the grammar format in a file and their LaTeX equivalents used for the parse tree in the output file.
    LexicalAnalyzer
    Scanner class, generated by JFlex.
    LexicalUnit
    Enum representing different types of lexical units.
    Main
    Main class parses a given input file and generates the parse tree of the input file in LaTeX.
    Parser
    Parser class is a recursive descent LL(1) parser that parses a given input file according to its action table and its context-free grammar.
    ParseTools
    ParseTools class contains all the tools related to grammars such as Firstk, Followk, Firstk(alphaFollowk(A)), LL(k) definition and LL(1) action table.
    ParseTree
    A skeleton class to represent parse trees.
    Rule
    Represents a rule in the grammar with its left-hand side, right-hand side and number.
    Symbol
    Represents tokens for the scanner and symbols (terminal or variable) for the grammar.
